<section class="bg-zinc-950 text-white py-16 px-6">
  <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto">
    <h2 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-bold text-brand-green mb-10 text-center">🔍 Scam Score™ Signals</h2>

    <div class="grid gap-8 sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3">
      <!-- Signal Card 1 -->
      <div class="bg-zinc-900 border border-zinc-700 rounded-2xl p-6 shadow-md">
        <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-brand-yellow mb-2">🚨 Urgent Language</h3>
        <p class="text-zinc-300  mb-2">Messages that pressure you to “act now” or threaten consequences.</p>
        <p class="text-zinc-400 text-sm italic mb-2">⚠ Why we flag this: Scammers use urgency to bypass rational thinking.</p>
        <p class="text-zinc-500 text-sm">Examples: “Immediate action required”, “Your account will be locked”, “Final warning”</p>
      </div>

      <!-- Signal Card 2 -->
      <div class="bg-zinc-900 border border-zinc-700 rounded-2xl p-6 shadow-md">
        <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-brand-yellow mb-2">🔗 Suspicious Links</h3>
        <p class="text-zinc-300 mb-2">Links that redirect through sketchy domains or mimic trusted brands.</p>
        <p class="text-zinc-400 text-sm italic mb-2">⚠ Why we flag this: Scam sites often hide behind deceptive URLs.</p>
        <p class="text-zinc-500 text-sm">Examples: Bit.ly links, misspelled domains like “go0gle.com”, or invisible redirects.</p>
      </div>

      <!-- Signal Card 3 -->
      <div class="bg-zinc-900 border border-zinc-700 rounded-2xl p-6 shadow-md">
        <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-brand-yellow mb-2">👤 Impersonation</h3>
        <p class="text-zinc-300 mb-2">Messages pretending to be from banks, government agencies, or well-known services.</p>
        <p class="text-zinc-400 text-sm italic mb-2">⚠ Why we flag this: Scammers rely on trust by posing as authority figures.</p>
        <p class="text-zinc-500 text-sm">Examples: “This is PayPal support”, “We are the IRS”, “Your Amazon account is compromised”</p>
      </div>

      <!-- Signal Card 4 -->
      <div class="bg-zinc-900 border border-zinc-700 rounded-2xl p-6 shadow-md">
        <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-brand-yellow mb-2">💰 Unrealistic Offers</h3>
        <p class="text-zinc-300 mb-2">Claims of free money, prizes, or job opportunities that seem too good to be true.</p>
        <p class="text-zinc-400 text-sm italic mb-2">⚠ Why we flag this: Scams prey on hope and curiosity with fake rewards.</p>
        <p class="text-zinc-500 text-sm">Examples: “You’ve won $1,000,000”, “Work from home and earn $500/day”, “Click to claim your prize”</p>
      </div>

      <!-- Signal Card 5 -->
      <div class="bg-zinc-900 border border-zinc-700 rounded-2xl p-6 shadow-md">
        <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-brand-yellow mb-2">📅 Unusual Timing</h3>
        <p class="text-zinc-300 mb-2">Messages sent at odd hours or with date/time inconsistencies.</p>
        <p class="text-zinc-400 text-sm italic mb-2">⚠ Why we flag this: Automation tools used by scammers often miss context clues like time zones.</p>
        <p class="text-zinc-500 text-sm">Examples: A “Friday” email sent on Sunday, or timestamps that don’t match sender’s location.</p>
      </div>

      <!-- Signal Card 6 -->
      <div class="bg-zinc-900 border border-zinc-700 rounded-2xl p-6 shadow-md">
        <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-brand-yellow mb-2">📎 Suspicious Attachments</h3>
        <p class="text-zinc-300 mb-2">Includes files like .zip, .exe, or documents with hidden macros.</p>
        <p class="text-zinc-400 text-sm italic mb-2">⚠ Why we flag this: Attachments can deliver malware, ransomware, or data theft tools.</p>
        <p class="text-zinc-500 text-sm">Examples: “invoice_4721.zip”, “Urgent.docm”, “tracking_file.exe”</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
